4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, members of the Board of
6 Pardons and Paroles serve six-year terms commencing on
7 July 1.
8 This bill would change the term start date from
9 July 1 to March 1.
10
11
12 A BILL
13 TO BE ENTITLED
14 AN ACT
15
16 Relating to the Board of Pardons and Paroles; to amend
17 Section 15-22-20, Code of Alabama 1975; to change the date on
18 which a member of the Board of Pardons and Paroles'
19 appointment commences from July 1 to March 1.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. Section 15-22-20, Code of Alabama 1975, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 "§15-22-20
24 (a) There shall be a Board of Pardons and Paroles which
25 shall consist that consists of three members. The membership
26 of the board shall be inclusive and reflect the racial,
27 gender, geographic, urban/rural urban, rural, or and economic
28 diversity of the state. At least one member shall be a current
