29 or former law enforcement officer with a minimum of 10 years'
30 experience in or with a law enforcement agency which that has
31 among its primary duties and responsibilities the
32 investigation of violent crimes or the apprehension, arrest,
33 or supervision of the perpetrators thereof.
34 (b) Any vacancy occurring on the board, whether for an
35 expired or unexpired term, shall be filled by appointment by
36 the Governor, with the advice and consent of the Senate, from
37 a list of five qualified persons nominated individuals
38 submitted by a board nominating committee consisting of the
39 Lieutenant Governor, the Speaker of the House of
40 Representatives, and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate.
41 The nominating board shall committee, as soon as practicable
42 after a vacancy occurs, whether for an expired or unexpired
43 term, shall meet and select by majority vote the names of five
44 persons individuals to be submitted to the Governor. The board
45 nominating committee shall immediately submit its nominations
46 to the Governor, who shall make his or her appointment from
47 the list within 10 days. Appointees shall begin serving
48 immediately upon appointment, until confirmed or rejected by
49 the Senate. Appointments made at times when the Senate is not
50 in regular session shall be effective ad interim. Any
51 appointment made by the Governor while the Senate is in
52 regular session must be submitted to the Senate not later than
53 the third legislative day following the date of the
54 appointment; any. Any appointment made while the Senate is not
55 in regular session shall be submitted not later than the third
56 legislative day following the reconvening of the Legislature
